Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the Culinary Workers Union Local 226 in Las Vegas, Nevada, expressing her support for organized labor and the rights of working people. She praised the union for their recent accomplishments, including a 32% pay raise over five years. Harris emphasized the importance of collective bargaining and fair outcomes in negotiations, stating that the strength of the nation depends on the strength of working people. She commended the union for their efforts to improve workplace safety and set new standards for workers across the country. Harris also emphasized the need for leaders to lift up others and show concern for the suffering of people. She thanked the union for their work and congratulated them on their achievements.